title: All Girls Garage
subTitle: Bogi and Faye get to play with some American muscle, as the girls bring in an all-new Dodge Challenger SRT Hellcat Widebody Redeye and add a Stage II power kit.

title: All Girls Garage
subTitle: The team brings back the 442 Tribute car to give it a new LS engine and finish modifying the interior for the previously-installed TKO transmission.

title: Car Fix
subTitle: The guys bring in a 1924 Model T hearse to get it running again, after it's spent the last 30 years in a museum. Then Fuller starts mocking up and building his Formula Ford race car.

title: Street Outlaws
subTitle: Chief commits to fall down the list on purpose to race everyone he missed on his last trip to the top. Also, Ryan and Chuck struggle to get their cars ready.

subTitle: Drew and Paul are seduced by a Lotus Esprit, a car made famous by a classic James Bond film. The project starts with a lover affair but becomes their biggest and most expensive restoration to date.

title: Bitchin' Rides: Road to the Ridler
subTitle: Dave and the crew start their all-aluminium Ridler build by creating a fibreglass buck; Dave realises there may be a problem with the roof.

title: Dirt Every Day
subTitle: Exploring and going on off road adventures, in a wide variety of different vehicles.

title: Dirt Every Day
subTitle: Fred and Dave head back to Alabama to redeem themselves in their revamped V-10 powered Rock Viper. This time they have improved it with better suspension, a new transfer case and a modified roll-cage.

title: Seduced by Speed
subTitle: Liz Carmichael believes an underpowered three-wheeled car can challenge Detroit's gas-guzzling behemoths of the 1970s; she launches a campaign to change how Americans think about cars -- until murder and deception sends Liz on the lam.
